 211:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c **** /* Lets other layers report a failure into this file's shared recovery
 212:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * ladder (see escalate_recovery()) instead of running their own independent
 213:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * power-cycle/start() decision. Two current callers:
 214:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *   - sx_user_mqtt.c's _on_publish(), after MQTT_PUBLISH_MAX_RETRY
 215:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     consecutive publish failures.
 216:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *   - sx_user_mqtt.c's _on_modem_error() (modem_ops_t.set_on_error callback),
 217:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     fired by the driver itself for: (a) the init-attach sequence never
 218:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     reaching ready in the first place (see a7677s.c's restart_init() gap
 219:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     fix), or (b) the periodic AT+CSQ heartbeat failing
 220:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     A7677S_MAX_RETRY times in a row while runtime-idle (see a7677s.c's
 221:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     csq_fail_count) — both are the driver's own signal that something is
 222:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     wrong, previously only logged and never coordinated with any recovery
 223:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  *     action.
 224:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * Deliberately does NOT set mqtt->state or fire on_disconnected: none of
 225:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * these failure reports by themselves prove the MQTT connection is down
 226:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * (state is driven by the real connect/disconnect/connlost paths elsewhere
 227:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * in this file) — this call only means "count this toward the shared
 228:SynaptiX_FDK/services/mqtt/sx_mqtt.c ****  * recovery ladder." */
